Vice President Biden spoke with Masoud Barzani, President of the Iraqi Kurdistan Region, about the importance of forming a new Iraqi government quickly. They agreed that the new government should address long-standing disputes between the central and regional governments in a fair and transparent manner, following the mechanisms set forth in the Iraqi constitution. They also discussed the need to resolve any territorial disputes arising from the current crisis peacefully and in consultation with all communities. Vice President Biden expressed sympathy for Kurdish Peshmerga fighters and Iraqi soldiers killed in battle against ISIL, and encouraged all political forces to unite against this threat.